[host] opening COM5 @ 115200
[host] draining for 1.0s
[cmd] help
[uart] help
[uart]   Commands:
[uart]     status | s          Full system status
[uart]     stop | q | exit     Clean shutdown and exit
[uart]     step <N>            Single-step N times
[uart]     checkpoint | cp     Stage active payload, then force WAL checkpoint
[uart]     read-site <idx>     Read A7 site (0-511)
[uart]     cmod-site <idx>     Read raw 512-site Cmod mirror site
[uart]     dump-wal            Read all 32 Cmod WAL sites
[uart]     dump-cmod [n]       Read raw Cmod mirror and print non-zero sites
[uart]     dump-all            Dump all 512 A7 sites
[uart]     wal-var-status      Read variable WAL metadata/caps
[uart]     wal-active          Show Z7 active variable WAL engine
[uart]     wal-var-config <words> <mask_hex> [checksum_hex]  Stage variable WAL metadata
[uart]     wal-var-write <idx> <word_hex> | wal-var-read <idx> [count]
[uart]     wal-var-dump [count] | wal-var-selftest  Verify Cmod variable WAL RAM
[uart]     wal-save-mts | wal-save-mts-checkpoint | wal-restore-mts
[uart]                          Save/restore MTS field+potential through WAL_VAR/flash
[uart]     wal-save-sha|robot|ukernel and wal-restore-sha|robot|ukernel
[uart]                          Save/restore accelerator/VM state through WAL_VAR/flash
[uart]                          Default checkpoint stages active MTS/SHA/robot/ukernel unless wal-bypass is ON
[uart]     restore             Manual restore from flash
[uart]     cold-start          Configure A7/Cmod from defaults/config
[uart]   Physics / timing:
[uart]     set tau-rate <hz>        Change tau tick rate live
[uart]     set spi1-div <n>         Set Z7->A7 SPI divider
[uart]     set spi0-div <n>         Set Z7->Cmod SPI divider
[uart]     set v2|eta|zeta|lambdaR|gamma|cg2|epsilon <hex>  A7 coefficient
[uart]     set tau-low|tau-high|tau-block <hex>   Anomaly thresholds
[uart]     set w-energy|w-curvature|step-size <hex>  Repair weights
[uart]     set push-period <n>      SPI3 push period
[uart]     set repair on|off        Enable/disable repair
[uart]     set logging on|off       Enable/disable WAL logging
[uart]     set recovery-fields 3|6  Select compact or six-field recovery
[uart]     set recovery-depth <n>   Set requested recovery depth (Cmod caps it)
[uart]     set wal-bypass on|off    Bypass Cmod step_done
[uart]     set particle-count <n>   Override Particle3D count before cold-start
[uart]     set particle-batch <n>   Override Particle3D batch size before cold-start
[uart]     set particle-seed <n>    Override Particle3D deterministic seed
[uart]     set particle-scale <hex> Override accelerator normalization scale
[uart]     set accum-mode full512|local27|local125|hist
[uart]     set accum-lanes <n>      Request Particle3D accumulation lanes
[uart]     set site-lanes <n>       Request Particle3D site/evolution lanes
[uart]     set wal-policy full|checkpoint|final|off-debug
[uart]     set binary-output-first on|off
[uart]   Site data:
[uart]     write-site <i> <psi> <prev> <m>   Write A7 site (Q16.16 hex)
[uart]     write-lambda <site> <val>          Write per-site lambdaR
[uart]     write-block <addr> <val>           Raw Cmod register write
[uart]   Flow control:
[uart]     pause                   Stop tau ticks; A7 may still report BUSY while waiting
[uart]     resume                  Restart tau using auto-step bootstrap
[uart]     tau-reset               Force tau auto-step bootstrap/reset
[uart]     layer-status | ls       Show derived adaptive layer plan and A7 descriptor
[uart]     layer-push [idx]        Write A7 descriptor for layer idx (default 0)
[uart]     particle-load [idx]     Load particle layer idx into A7 and pause
[uart]     particle-start          Run Particle3D hardware accumulation now
[uart]     particle-status         Read Particle3D accelerator status
[uart]     particle-clear          Clear Particle3D done/error status
[uart]   MTS full-physics kernels:
[uart]     mts-config 1d <particles> <gx> [timesteps]     Auto-sets dt/diffusion/vcoeff/dx
[uart]     mts-config 2d <particles> <gx> <gy> [timesteps]
[uart]     mts-config 3d <particles> <gx> <gy> <gz> [timesteps]
[uart]     mts-coeff <dt_q16> <diffusion_q16> <v_coeff_q16>  Override coefficients
[uart]     mts-normalize on|off       Enable/disable per-timestep normalization
[uart]     mts-init [grid_size [width]]  ARM computes Gaussian IC, loads field+potential
[uart]        Defaults: grid_size=100 width=0.1. Uses the active 1D/2D/3D shape.
[uart]     mts-load-field <idx> <real_q16> <imag_q16>  Manual single-site field load
[uart]     mts-load-potential <idx> <q16>              Manual single-site potential load
[uart]     mts-load-potential-all <q16>                Fill active potential table
[uart]     mts-load-layer <particle_base> <count>  Load deterministic Q16 occupancy field
[uart]     mts-start               Start configured 1D/2D/3D MTS kernel
[uart]     mts-start-field-dump [n]  Start and dump final Q16 field in one command
[uart]     wal-var-mts-restore-start-field-dump <words> <checksum_hex> [n]
[uart]     mts-status              Poll full MTS status/cycles/active shape/contract
[uart]     mts-read <idx>          Read one complex i64 result entry
[uart]     mts-dump [count]        Dump up to 1024 result entries as decimal real/imag
[uart]     mts-field-read <idx>    Read one final Q16 field entry
[uart]     mts-field-dump [count]  Dump final Q16 field entries
[uart]     mts-clear               Clear MTS done/error status
[uart]     mts-reset               Reset MTS kernel control state
[uart]     mts-bench               Print MTS cycle and cycles/point/step counters
[uart]   FLX lattice layout / expansion routing:
[uart]     layout-status           Read mapper contract, mode, shape, coordinate, local index
[uart]     layout-set row|snake|morton  Select row-major, serpentine, or Morton/Z-order mapper
[uart]     layout-map <dim> <gx> [gy] [gz] <x> [y] [z]  Map logical coordinate to local index
[uart]     layout-dump [count]     Print first logical coordinates mapped through active layout
[uart]     route-status | route-map  Read Z7-mediated expansion route mailbox
[uart]     route-read <board> <idx> | route-write <board> <idx> <word_hex>
[uart]   GMW Universal Kernel v1:
[uart]     ukernel-caps | ukernel-status  Read VM contract/status/cycles/hashes
[uart]     ukernel-config <active> [sx] [sy] [sz] [flags_hex]  Stage VM shape, no start
[uart]     ukernel-load-prog halt|sum4     Load built-in VM program slot
[uart]     ukernel-load-prog <idx> <word_hex>  Load raw 32-bit VM instruction
[uart]     ukernel-load-data <idx> <word_hex>  Load VM data RAM
[uart]     ukernel-load-const <idx> <word_hex> Load VM constant RAM
[uart]     ukernel-start | ukernel-step [n]    Run or single-step VM
[uart]     ukernel-read <idx> [count] | ukernel-dump [count]  Read VM data RAM
[uart]     ukernel-hash-state | ukernel-bench  Hash/report VM state
[uart]     ukernel-clear | ukernel-reset | ukernel-restore-test
[uart]   SHA / robotics accelerator slots:
[uart]     sha-config <nonce_start> <nonce_count>
[uart]     sha-load-header <idx0-19> <word_hex>  Load big-endian SHA header word
[uart]     sha-start | sha-status | sha-clear | sha-reset
[uart]     robot-config <active> <gx> <gy> <steps> [flags_hex]
[uart]     robot-load <idx> <cell_word_hex> | robot-read <idx> [count]
[uart]     robot-start | robot-status | robot-hash-state | robot-clear | robot-reset
[uart]     accel-status            Show accelerator mode, lanes, progress, cycles
[uart]     accel-caps              Show compiled accelerator capabilities
[uart]     benchmark-status        Show accelerator + evolution benchmark counters
[uart]     reset-stats             Clear repair/error counters
[uart]     clear-errors            Clear sticky Z7 error flags
[uart]     drain-ack               Force one Cmod WAL drain acknowledgement
[uart]     clear-backpressure      Pause tau and force Cmod checkpoint/drain
[uart]     bp-recover              Alias for clear-backpressure
[uart]     BTN2/L20                Hardware button: clear backpressure, wait 0.5s, resume
[uart]   Files:
[uart]     snapshot <file>         Save state to file
[uart]     load <file>             Load state from file into A7
[uart]     sd-ls [path]            List SD directory with size/CRC
[uart]     sd-cat <file>           Print small SD text file
[uart]     sd-get <file>           Emit binary file as CRC checked chunks
[uart]     sd-get-dir <path>       Enumerate files for host pull tool
[uart]     particle-superpose [n]  Run Particle3D A7 hardware accumulation, optionally limited to n particles
[uart]   Monitor:
[uart]     monitor on|off          Stream status every poll
[uart]     monitor rate <ms>       Set monitor print interval
[uart]     log-energy on|off       Toggle per-tick energy log
[uart]   Diagnostics:
[uart]     energy-check | ec      Pause tau, scan A7 site RAM, compare SW energy to HW regs
[uart]     wal-bypass on|off       Bypass Cmod step_done
[uart]     regs                    Dump all Z7 PL registers
[uart]     spi-health              Test SPI1/SPI0 links
[uart]     force-spi3              Push A7 state to Cmod and print Cmod SPI3 counters
[uart]     a7-debug                Dump A7 first-step/engine debug registers
[uart]     button status is included in regs (btn[2] is L20 recovery)
[uart]     read-reg  <hex>         Raw Z7 register read
[uart]     write-reg <hex> <hex>   Raw Z7 register write
[uart]     a7-reg  <hex>           SPI1 read to A7 register
[uart]     cmod-reg <hex>          SPI0 read to Cmod register
[uart]   General:
[uart]     status|s  step <N>  checkpoint|cp  dump-wal  dump-all
[uart]     restore   cold-start   stop|q    help|h
